one get their FA (that's what coffee and sick days are for).<br><br>As far as a date, the earliest for me would be the 19th.  I have a pretty hectic travel schedule this month (I'm writing this from my hotel room in Denver), and things wont settle down much til then.<br><br>Keep me posted,<br><br>Faltan <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uleolan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Leolan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_bluespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle><FONT COLOR=AA0000><B>Lanys.com Administrator</B></FONT></span><br> <font color=#000033>(1/7/02 8:13:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumpaladin.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=322.topic&index=10>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://129.171.140.2/leo/leopic.asp WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A Proposal for the FA</span><hr size=1> Highest levels you can get.  24 people max.  Don't bring 5 paladins.  SC them up when you're on Pegasus Isle.  That's my advice. <p> - Leo<br> <a href="mailto:leolan@lanys.com">leolan@lanys.com</a><p><small>"You must be willing to fail if you want to succeed."</small></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uhaladrimdragonheart.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Haladrim Dragonheart</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>l33t d00d!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(1/8/02 5:10:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumpaladin.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=322.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A Proposal for the FA</span><hr size=1>      Leo ... do you know how to summon a paly on 4th ??? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>If we can do for one, we can do for many hehe <br><br>   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ukalamad.showPublicProfile?language=EN>kalamad</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>w4nn4b3!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(1/8/02 5:47:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumpaladin.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=322.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A Proposal for the FA</span><hr size=1> Summon, from what I think and believe (have never done this btw, so I could be wrong, feel free to correct me)<br><br>When groups has reached Pegasus Isle, A Wizard and Necro group (Wizard leads). Wizard comes to Toxx and invites the people that want to go up and port up, then the people that need to die, die there - wizzy might want to leave first).<br>Wizzy then picks us up in Toxx again and ports up the next time.<br><br>There we have a group with all the people needed to summon the corpses to the pegasus isle <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br><br>And I believe that the keys are no rent, but stick around for the wizzy after all this, if he wants to return to the hunting party <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br><br>edit: typo <p><br>-------------------------<br>Kalamad Wolfrunner<br>54th season Paladin<br>Arma Aquetatis</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ukalamad.showPublicProfile?language=EN>kalamad</A> at: 1/8/02 5:48:11 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/usirarris.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sir Arris</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Knight of Truth</span><br> <font color=#000033>(1/8/02 6:01:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumpaladin.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=322.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A Proposal for the FA</span><hr size=1> <br>Necromancer and wizard are grouped on the 5th isle of the Plane of Air (wizard will lead the group). The wizard goes to the Toxx wizard spire (or another spire/platform of your choice). Wizard ports up along with 4 more new members he invited. New people die, necro uses the group party box thing to target the corpses on the 1st isle, summons the corpse, cleric resses. This is how people are moved between isles without keys.<br><br>So the only thing Kalamad was slightly off on was the keys. While the keys are <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  not</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> technically NO RENT, there is a snitch however. The keys will vanish from your inventory if you try to take them out of the Plane. IE, you can camp out now and have your key on your person indefinately, though the second you zone with the key on your avatar, /bye.<br><br>EDIT: DISCLAIMER! The second paragraph is from my own personal experiences with the PoA keys when I went to attain my FA, which was quite a while ago. I haven't heard about anything other then some drops/quest rewards being changed there since then, though I could be wrong and it is different now. If anyone with more recent experience in Air has some more accurate information, please feel free to correct me. <p><center><hr width=450> <font face="Engravers MT"><a href=http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.as